# Notifications

Push notification system using OneSignal. All infrastructure, including tap routing, lives in `core/notifications/`, but routing stays app-agnostic by injecting paths from outside core.

## File structure
```
lib/
  core/
    notifications/
      notification_types.dart            # NotificationType enum + data classes + AppNotification
      notification_storage.dart          # SharedPreferences persistence
      notification_service.dart          # OneSignal singleton
      notification_router.dart           # Route map injected via configure()
      foreground_notification_banner.dart
      notifications.dart                 # Barrel export
```

---

## NotificationType

icon and color live on the enum — no utility class needed.

```dart
notification.type.icon   // IconData
notification.type.color  // Color
```

### Adding a new notification type
1. Add to NotificationType enum with string value
2. Add icon and color switch cases
3. Create NotificationData subclass with fromJson using Helper.get*()
4. Add to NotificationData.fromJson factory switch
5. Handle in NotificationRouter.route() switch
6. Add serialization in NotificationStorage._dataToJson()

---

## NotificationService

Singleton. Wire up the tap handler after initialization:

```dart
// In AuthBuilder after Authenticated
await NotificationService.instance.initialize(appId: Env.oneSignalAppId, context: context);
NotificationService.instance.onNotificationTapped = (n) => NotificationRouter.route(context, n);
await NotificationService.instance.setupUserAfterAuth();

// On logout
await NotificationService.instance.clearUserData();
```

The onNotificationTapped callback keeps core/ decoupled from app routes.

### Available methods
All return Result<T>:
- getNotifications()              Result<List<AppNotification>>
- getUnreadCount()                Result<int>
- markNotificationAsRead(id)      Result<void>
- clearAllNotifications()         Result<void>
- areNotificationsEnabled()       Result<bool>
- requestPermission()             Result<bool>
- getPlayerId()                   Result<String?>

---

## NotificationRouter

Routes notification taps to GoRouter paths using a map configured from outside core. Never called from views.

```dart
// Configure once after authentication (e.g. in AuthBuilder)
NotificationRouter.configure({
  NotificationType.paymentReceived: '/home',
  NotificationType.moneyRequest: '/home',
  NotificationType.newLearningVideo: '/learning',
  NotificationType.customCommunication: '/home',
});

NotificationService.instance.onNotificationTapped =
    (n) => NotificationRouter.route(context, n);
```

`route` looks up the path for `notification.type`, falls back to `/home` if none is registered, and calls `context.go(path, extra: notification.data)`.

---

## NotificationStorage

Static methods only — no instantiation. All return Result<T>.

---

## ForegroundNotificationBanner

Display-only. Routing happens via NotificationService.onNotificationTapped — never inside the banner.

---

## Rules
- Never use print() or logging package — use debugLog() from core/helpers.dart
- Always use Success() / Failure() — never Result.success() / Result.failure()
- Always use Helper.get*() for JSON parsing — never raw casts
- notification_router.dart lives in core/notifications/ — routes injected via configure(), never hardcoded inside
- Never call NotificationRouter.route() from views — wire it via onNotificationTapped
- NotificationService is a singleton — always NotificationService.instance
- ForegroundNotificationBanner is display-only — no routing logic inside it
